title: Impulse and Relativity target 2026 for launch of first Mars lander mission
summary: Two companies are preparing for a 2026 launch of what they believe will be the first commercial robotic Mars lander mission, the start of what the companies plan to be a regular series of such missions.

title: Fleet Space secures $33 million for mineral exploration constellation
summary: Fleet Space Technologies has raised around $33 million in a Series C round to expand its satellite-based mineral exploration services.

title: NASA, Department of Education Partnership Strengthens STEM Education
summary: NASA and the U.S. Department of Education signed a memorandum of understanding on Wednesday, strengthening the collaboration between the two agencies, including efforts to increase access to high-quality STEM and space education to students and schools across the nation.

title: BlackSky, Spire roll out space-based maritime tracking service
summary: BlackSky and Spire Global announced May 24 they are offering a new monitoring service that tracks ships via satellites.

title: No one should be surprised Virgin Orbit failed—it had a terrible business plan
summary: The business case simply did not close.
